snippet.title: J. Cole - The Climb Back (Official Audio)
snippet.description:
J. Cole - Lewis Street is available now: https://JCole.lnk.to/LewisStreet/
Produced by J. Cole

Everything come back around full circle 
Why do lies sound pleasant but the truth hurtful
Everybody gotta cry once in a while 
But how long will it take before you smile
This is that come back to life shit
My niggas pick me up and we gon light the city up as if the sun had the night shift 
And paint the town red for my nigga found dead to soon

Yea 
To the left of that decimal I need 7 figures to play the joint
Turn up your decibels peep how I decimate a joint 
Check out my projects like them workers that section 8 appoints 
And you’ll see how I flipped, like exclamation points 
My niggas shoot first as if they never played the point, more 2 guards 
Enough straps to fill four uhauls
More death than World War II caused around these parts
We pour the brown just to drown these thoughts
Of black corpses in county morgues, Lord, those images hauntin 
I ain’t been sleep yet, it’s 10 in the morning 
I’m sending a warning, a problem with me is like the BET hip hop awards I’m starting to see you niggas don’t want it 
I’m sick of this flauntin, from niggas I know for sho ain’t got mo dough than Cole
Trash rappers Ass backwards tryna go toe to toe
We laugh at ya, staff strapped up on top the totem pole 
To blast at ya, 
Bass masters, look how they tote a pole 
Gotta know the ropes and the protocol 
Or they gon for sho blow your clothes half off like a promo code 
Made a lil tune called folding clothes, and a nigga still ain’t known to fold
Under pressure, well you know what coal do
Make a diamond, they just rhymin, me I’m quoting gold
1 phone call Get you cancelled like a homophobe,
In this PC culture, address me as the goat, like they call chief Keef Sosa, in my sectional like a fuckin 3 piece sofa
Im known as the chosen one, 
Another dead body lay frozen that’s how it go sometimes 
When Niggas weighing coke just like the pro’s and cons 
Well I ain’t with that sleeping underground like a gopher, so I go for mines

Everything come back around full circle 
Why do lies sound pleasant but the truth hurtful
Everybody gotta cry once in a while 
But how long will it take before you smile
This is that come back to life shit
My niggas pick me up and we gon light the city up as if the sun had the night shift 
And paint the town red for my nigga found dead to soon
Now I know why they call it Blue (YEAAAA)

Survival at all costs, everyday niggas get logged off 
Bodies Get hauled off 
Passing a funeral procession While holding my breath in the car I thought 
At times it be feelin the devil be winning but do that mean god lost 
Just got off the phone with my nigga he back in the kennel my dog lost 
I brought him round close to me
Before but he
Became addicted to clout and all the hoes we’d meet 
I slowly peeped,
Jealousy on his breath, whenever he spoke to me 
Like on the low he feeling like in my shoes is where he sposed to be 
I tried to ignore the signs, but there in the back of my mind it felt
Like letting a nigga come sleep on your couch but he eating up all yo groceries 
My nigga repeated this quote to me, I felt it’s potency 
Said Most of these, niggas gon hang theyselfs, just give em the rope and see 
I headed that, and what got showed to me
Was screaming that, some niggas you gotta leave em back unfortunately,
We seen the trap, niggas be on that demon clock resultantly
They fiend to clap, as often as the genius app misquotin me  
Meanwhile, I see that yo diamonds is glistening 
I’m Glad that you shining but need I remind you my niggas is diamond and nickeling 
Scraping up whatever coin they can find, the pettiest crime they committing it
Just to get by for a limited time, the Steepest of mountains they tryna climb 
I’m here tryna find the derivative 
You niggas don’t feel me,
You see the clout
You don’t see the real me
If I was sick, you niggas wouldn’t heal me 
Therefore I’m healin myself, getting in tune with my God, slowly revealing myself, building my wealth, a nigga touch mine ima kill em myself

Everything come back around full circle 
Why do lies sound pleasant but the truth hurtful
Everybody gotta cry once in a while 
But how long will it take before you smile
This is that come back to life shit
My niggas pick me up and we gon light the city up as if the sun had the night shift 
And paint the town red for my nigga found dead to soon
Now I know why they call it Blue (YEAAAA)

snippet.title: J. Cole - Lion King On Ice (Official Audio)
snippet.description:
J. Cole - Lewis Street is available now: https://JCole.lnk.to/LewisStreet/
Produced by J. Cole, T-Minus, and Jetson

I got Blood on my hands I ain’t gon lie
I got mud on my shoes 
I got real real big plans I ain’t gon lie
Gotta whole to prove I ain’t gon lie 

I got Blood on my hands I ain’t gon lie
I got mud on my shoes 
I got real real big plans I ain’t gon lie
Gotta whole to prove I ain’t gon lie 

Sip from the bottle for shit that we bottling in
Going live but we not on the gram 
This the land of supply and demand
Where my young niggas choppin up grams 
And them choppers won’t pry from they hands 
Packing lead like they got a exam
If it’s beef my niggas look just like home wreckers, they got they eye on your man
I Pray to god that it jam
too many done died in these parts so we gotta be smart if we tryna see August 
some niggas won’t make past summer regardless 
I’m trying my hardest to stack my deposits these niggas be lookin at me like I got it 
Deep down inside tho I still feel as broke as that nigga who just graduated from college
Scrappin up change that got left in my pockets 
I’m Tryna make nickles turn into a dollar 
Riding the train way too shy to go holla 
Just watched her get off at her stop I’m a coward 
Fuck it tho you got a way bigger target 
Ima do it so big they won’t know what to call it
Sound like a whole lambo truck in my stomach
Bitch I ain’t hungry this feeling is starvin 
Gotta move momma from out them apartments
Gotta put Ville on the map we forgotten 
Gotta hit hoes you hang up in yo locker 
Gotta get rich cuz my granny picked cotton,
Gotta make hits cuz if not then I’m floppin
Gotta stay me in the process,
Niggas dissed me it was nonsense,
I sat em down like his father,
My nigga asked why you bother 
We shoulda caught em and mobbed em
I said we gotta move smarter 
Don’t wan be the reason for one more sad song 
I tried to warn niggas they wouldn’t last song
I hope that you see how they came and they went
They shots never hit but they made they attempts 
May have a good year like that name on the blimp
But you know what it take to be poppin this long?
Dedication on another level niggas never seen in they life 
Celebrating all your first downs like they touch downs bring a price 
Young Simba had the bust down yea the lion king on ice 
Niggas wanted me to look the part, Had to stop to takin advice
Put the jewelry to the side, had to find me had to find god
Half the time we be pacifying what they expect from us 
But that’s treacherous 
That shows less of us,
I need y’all to see,
Every part of me,
Every scar and 
And every arterie,
Every story that I can recall 
And then I can fall

I got Blood on my hands I ain’t gon lie
I got mud on my shoes 
I got real real big plans I ain’t gon lie
Gotta whole to prove I ain’t gon lie 

I got Blood on my hands I ain’t gon lie
I got mud on my shoes 
I got real real big plans I ain’t gon lie
Gotta whole to prove I ain’t gon lie 

Lately I reflect 
On the times a nigga was low 
I Got it up off the floor
I’m Stronger than ever before
I’m stronger than ever before
Just like I planned to be
They wanna see see me fold
It ain’t no thang to me

Thoughts when I was broke
If only I could be
Pockets holding hope 
It ain’t no thang to meeeee
At night I hit my knees 
I prayed for better days 
Then found a better me 
I got my head on straight

snippet.title: MAGIC at CLIPPERS | SCRIMMAGE HIGHLIGHTS | July 22, 2020
snippet.description:
MAGIC at CLIPPERS | SCRIMMAGE HIGHLIGHTS | July 22, 2020

The LA Clippers defeated the Orlando Magic, 99-90. Lou Williams recorded a game-high 22 PTS for the LA Clippers, while Paul George added 18 PTS, 5 REB and 3 AST in the victory. Nikola Vucevic led the Magic with 18 PTS and 10 REB. #WholeNewGame

The NBA Restart begins July 30th with daily and nightly games on TNT, ESPN, ABC, NBA TV and NBA League Pass.

snippet.title: Summer Morning Routine! *POPULAR GIRL vs NERDY BOY*
snippet.description:

The girl is super girly and loves to have a long morning workout. She loves to pamper herself with a long shower. She has her shaving routine, hair care routine and of course her summer make up routine for a fun day at the beach. However, the boy, Raja, wakes up bright and early and loves to catch up on some reading and summer homework. He makes his way to his job and of course visits his crush at work. snippet.title: BAD BUNNY – Artist Spotlight Stories
snippet.description:
Produced by YouTube Music and directed by Kristian Mercado, Bad Bunny’s Artist Spotlight Story is a psychedelic portrait of a global superstar unlike any other. The film explores Bad Bunny’s origins in Puerto Rico, manifesting his dreams into reality, and how he uses his platform to speak out against social issues, all brought to life through vibrant animations and cutting-edge visuals to reflect his visionary aesthetic.

This spotlight story was filmed before the pandemic.
BAD BUNNY –  Youtube Music Artist Spotlight Stories

snippet.title: Iced Tea 4 Ways - You Suck at Cooking (episode 112)
snippet.description:
Iced tea is very easy to make. It’s not as easy as hot tea on account of not having to subtract the heat from the tea once you make it which is an extra step. Unless you make cold brewed ice tea which takes forever which could be considered more difficult. When you want iced tea you want it now and there’s no need to wait. Except for the time it takes to make the iced tea because there’s no getting around that.
